    public class Pair<X,Y>
extends java.lang.Object
    The Pair class can be used to store two different values of individual types.

      • indexByFirst

        public static <A,B> int indexByFirst(java.util.List<Pair<A,B>> values,
                                     A key)
        Given a List of Pair values, and a key to seek, find the index of the first Pair whose first-value matches the key. If for any reason it can't be found, -1 is returned.
        Type Parameters:
        A - type of the first-field
        B - type of the second-field
        Parameters:
        values - The list of pairs to be searched.
        key - The value to compare with the first part of each pair in values.
        Returns:
        Index of the first pair in the list with first value that matches key.
